Use claude-router-auto for everything by default — the heuristic router picks
the right backend per request (local Qwen / remote Qwen / Claude escalation).

Pin a specific backend only when you know better than the router:
  - claude-qwen-coding   : local Qwen 3.6 27B on M4 Max (low latency)
  - claude-qwen-remote   : remote Qwen 3.6 35B-A3B on Strix Halo (heavier)
  - claude-escalation    : real Claude Sonnet (rare, expensive, hard reasoning)

Prefer tool calling over inline code suggestions.
Enable thinking mode for multi-file refactors and design-level questions.
